"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);


TEXT(beginproblem());

$b=random(1,5,1);
$a=random($b+1,$b+2,1);
$c=random($a+1,$a+2,1);
$apb = $a+$b;
$ab=$a*$b;
$apc = $a+$c;
$ac=$a*$c;

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
Cancel common polynomial and integer factors.  
and fill in the blanks.
$BR
\(\frac{x^2-$apb x + $ab}{x^2-$apc x + $ac} =
( x -\)
\{ ans_rule(3) \} 
\( ) \) 
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($b, mode=>"strict"));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
\( / (x - \)
\{ ans_rule(3) \} 
\( ) \) 
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($c, mode=>"strict"));

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT)); 
$BR
For this identity to hold, \(x\) must not equal
\{ ans_rule(3) \}.
EOT
ANS(num_cmp($a, mode=>"strict"));

TEXT(EV3(<<'EOT')); 
$BR Hint: If you have difficulties
seeing how to factor the numerator and denominator set them to zero,
solve the resulting equation, and deduce the appropriate linear
factors from the solution.  Then cancel the common factor in numerator
and denominator.

EOT

SOLUTION(EV3(<<'EOT'));
$BR $BBOLD Solution:$EBOLD
We have
\[\frac{x^2-$apb x + $ab}{x^2-$apc x + $ac} =
 \frac{(x-$a)(x-$b)}{(x-$a)(x-$c)} 
=  \frac{(x-$b)}{(x-$c)}\]

Since we canceled the factor \((x-$a) \), \(x\) must not equal \($a\).

EOT





